Docspell

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 0.17.1
This is the remote API to Docspell, a personal document organizer.

Attachment

secAttachmentIdArchiveGet

Get an attachment archive file.

Get the archive file that was originally uploaded that contains the attachment with the given id. If the attachment was not uploaded as part of an archive, a 404 is returned. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/archive

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/octet-stream"\
"/api/v1/sec/attachment/{id}/archive"

        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)

    }

secAttachmentIdArchiveHead

Get an attachment archive file.

Get information about the archive that contains the attachment with the given id. If the attachment was not uploaded as part of an archive, 404 is returned. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/archive

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secAttachmentIdDelete

Delete an attachment.

Deletes a single attachment with all its related data like file, the original file, extracted text, results from analysis etc. If the attachment is part of an archive, the archive is only deleted, if it is the last entry left. Archives are otherwise not deleted, if there are remaining attachments available. 


/sec/attachment/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X DELETE\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/sec/attachment/{id}"

Get the original binary file of the attachment with the given id. If the attachment is a converted PDF file, this route gets the original file as it was uploaded. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/original

secAttachmentIdPreviewGet

Get a preview image of an attachment file.

Gets a image file showing a preview of the attachment. Usually it is a small image of the first page of the document.If not available, a 404 is returned. However, if the query parameter `withFallback` is `true`, a fallback preview image is returned. You can also use the `HEAD` method to check for existence. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/preview

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/octet-stream"\
"/api/v1/sec/attachment/{id}/preview?withFallback="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.AttachmentApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AttachmentApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        AttachmentApi apiInstance = new AttachmentApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        Boolean withFallback = true; // Boolean | Whether to provide a fallback or not.
        try {
            byte[] result = apiInstance.secAttachmentIdPreviewGet(id, withFallback);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AttachmentApi#secAttachmentIdPreviewGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

secAttachmentIdPreviewPost

(Re)generate a preview image.

Submits a task that generates a preview image for this attachment. The existing preview will be replaced. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/preview

secAttachmentIdViewGet

A preview of the attachment

This provides a preview of the attachment. It currently uses a third-party javascript library (viewerjs) to display the preview. This works by redirecting to the viewerjs url with the attachment url as parameter. Note that the resulting url that is redirected to is not stable. It may change from version to version. This route, however, is meant to provide a stable url for the preview. 


/sec/attachment/{id}/view

secItemIdPreviewGet

Get a preview image of an attachment file.

Gets a image file showing a preview of the item. Usually it is a small image of the first page of the first attachment. If not available, a 404 is returned. However, if the query parameter `withFallback` is `true`, a fallback preview image is returned. You can also use the `HEAD` method to check for existence. 


/sec/item/{id}/preview

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/octet-stream"\
"/api/v1/sec/item/{id}/preview?withFallback="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.AttachmentApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AttachmentApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        AttachmentApi apiInstance = new AttachmentApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        Boolean withFallback = true; // Boolean | Whether to provide a fallback or not.
        try {
            byte[] result = apiInstance.secItemIdPreviewGet(id, withFallback);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AttachmentApi#secItemIdPreviewGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Whether to provide a fallback or not.

Responses

Status: 200 - Ok

  • Schema

secItemIdPreviewHead

Get a preview image of an attachment file.

Checks if an image file showing a preview of the item is available. If not available, a 404 is returned. The preview is currently the an image of the first page of the first attachment. 


/sec/item/{id}/preview

Authentication

openAuthLoginPost

Authenticate with account name and password.

Authenticate with account name and password. The account name is comprised of the collective id and user id separated by slash, backslash or whitespace. If successful, an authentication token is returned that can be used for subsequent calls to protected routes. 


/open/auth/login

Usage and SDK Samples

    }

Authentication with a token

Authenticate with a token. This can be used to get a new authentication token based on another valid one. 


/sec/auth/session

Collective

secCollectiveClassifierStartoncePost

Starts the learn-classifier task

If the collective has classification enabled, this will submit the task for learning a classifier from existing data. This task is usally run periodically as determined by the collective settings. The request is empty, settings are used from the collective. 


/sec/collective/classifier/startonce

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secCollectivePreviewsPost

Starts the generate previews task

Submits a task that re-generates preview images of all attachments of the current collective. Each existing preview image will be replaced. This can be used after changing the `preview` settings. If only preview images of selected attachments should be regenerated, see the `/sec/attachment/{id}/preview` endpoint. 


/sec/collective/previews

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/sec/collective/previews"

import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CollectiveApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        CollectiveApi apiInstance = new CollectiveApi();
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.secCollectivePreviewsPost();

secCustomfieldIdPut

Change a custom field

Change properties of a custom field. Changing the label has no further impliciations, since it is only used for displaying. The name and type on the other hand have consequences: name must be unique and the type determines how the value is stored internally. 


/sec/customfield/{id}

secEmailSendNameIdPost

Send an email.

Sends an email as specified in the body of the request. The item's attachment are added to the mail if requested. 


/sec/email/send/{name}/{id}

secEmailSettingsImapGet

List email settings for current user.

List all available e-mail settings for the current user. E-Mail settings specify imap connections that can be used to retrieve e-mails. Multiple e-mail settings can be specified, they are distinguished by their `name`. The query `q` parameter does a simple substring search in the connection name. 


/sec/email/settings/imap

Responses

secEmailSettingsSmtpGet

List email settings for current user.

List all available e-mail settings for the current user. E-Mail settings specify smtp connections that can be used to sent e-mails. Multiple e-mail settings can be specified, they are distinguished by their `name`. The query `q` parameter does a simple substring search in the connection name. 


/sec/email/settings/smtp

/sec/equipment

secFolderGet

Get a list of folders.

Return a list of folders for the current collective. All folders are returned, including those not owned by the current user. It is possible to restrict the results by a substring match of the name. 


/sec/folder

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/sec/folder?q=&full="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FolderApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FolderApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        FolderApi apiInstance = new FolderApi();
        String q = q_example; // String | A query string.
        Boolean full = true; // Boolean | Whether to get owning folders
        try {
            FolderList result = apiInstance.secFolderGet(q, full);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FolderApi#secFolderGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    $result = $api_instance->secFolderGet($q, $full);
    print_r($result);
} catch (Exception $e) {
    echo 'Exception when calling FolderApi->secFolderGet: ', $e->getMessage(), PHP_EOL;
}

    print Dumper($result);
};

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import swagger_client
from swagger_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
swagger_client.configuration.api_key['X-Docspell-Auth'] = 'YOUR_API_KEY'
# Uncomment below to setup prefix (e.g. Bearer) for API key, if needed
# swagger_client.configuration.api_key_prefix['X-Docspell-Auth'] = 'Bearer'

# create an instance of the API class
api_instance = swagger_client.FolderApi()
q = q_example # String | A query string. (optional)
full = true # Boolean | Whether to get owning folders (optional)

try: 
    # Get a list of folders.
    api_response = api_instance.sec_folder_get(q=q, full=full)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling FolderApi->secFolderGet: %s\n" % e)

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FolderApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FolderApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        FolderApi apiInstance = new FolderApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.secFolderIdDelete(id);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FolderApi#secFolderIdDelete");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

// Delete a folder by its id.
[apiInstance secFolderIdDeleteWith:id
              completionHandler: ^(BasicResult output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.FolderApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FolderApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        FolderApi apiInstance = new FolderApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        String userId = userId_example; // String | An identifier
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.secFolderIdMemberUserIdDelete(id, userId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FolderApi#secFolderIdMemberUserIdDelete");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

secFolderPost

Create a new folder

Create a new folder owned by the current user. If a folder with the same name already exists, an error is thrown. 


/sec/folder

FullTextIndex

openFtsReIndexAllIdPost

Re-creates the full-text index.

Clears the full-text index and inserts all data from the database. This migh take a while to complete. The response returns immediately. A task is submitted that will be executed by a job executor. Note that this affects all data of all collectives. The `id` is required and refers to the key given in the config file to ensure that only admins can call this route. 


/open/fts/reIndexAll/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/open/fts/reIndexAll/{id}"

secFtsReIndexPost

Re-creates the full-text index for the current collective

Clears the full-text index for all data belonging to the current collective and inserts the data from the database. The response is immediately returned and a task is submitted that will be executed by a job executor. 


/sec/fts/reIndex

IntegrationEndpoint

openIntegrationCheckfileIdChecksumGet

Check if a file is in docspell.

Checks if a file with the given SHA-256 checksum is in docspell. The `id` is the *collective name*. This route only exists, if it is enabled in the configuration file. The result shows all items that contains a file with the given checksum. 


/open/integration/checkfile/{id}/{checksum}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/open/integration/checkfile/{id}/{checksum}"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.IntegrationEndpointApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class IntegrationEndpointApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        IntegrationEndpointApi apiInstance = new IntegrationEndpointApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        String checksum = checksum_example; // String | A SHA-256 checksum
        try {
            CheckFileResult result = apiInstance.openIntegrationCheckfileIdChecksumGet(id, checksum);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling IntegrationEndpointApi#openIntegrationCheckfileIdChecksumGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

openIntegrationItemIdGet

Check if integration endpoint is available.

Allows to check whether an integration endpoint is enabled for a collective. The collective is given by the `id` parameter. It returns not found (404) if the endpoint is disabled (either globally by an admin or by a specific collective). It returns 403 (or 401 if http-basic is enabled) if authorization fails. The response body is empty (an empty json object). 


/open/integration/item/{id}

openIntegrationItemIdPost

Upload files to docspell.

Upload a file to docspell for processing. The id is a *collective name*. This route only exists, if enabled by an admin in the configuration. The route might be protected by different methods, all configurable via the configuration: - A specific header must be prestent - username/password via HTTP Basic mechanism - a specific source ip Files are submitted for processing to the specified collective, which eventually resuts in an item in their inbox. The request must be a `multipart/form-data` request, where the first part has name `meta`, is optional and may contain upload metadata as JSON. Checkout the structure `ItemUploadMeta` at the end if it is not shown here. Other parts specify the files. Multiple files can be specified, but at least on is required. 


/open/integration/item/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

-H "Accept: application/json"\
-H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data"\
"/api/v1/open/integration/item/{id}"

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        IntegrationEndpointApi apiInstance = new IntegrationEndpointApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        ItemUploadMeta meta = ; // ItemUploadMeta | 
        array[byte[]] file = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.openIntegrationItemIdPost(id, meta, file);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling IntegrationEndpointApi#openIntegrationItemIdPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Item

secItemConvertallpdfsPost

Convert all non-converted pdfs.

Submits a job that will find all pdf files that have not been converted and converts them using the ocrmypdf tool (if enabled). This tool has been added in version 0.9.0 and so older files can be "migrated" this way, or maybe after enabling the tool. The task finds all files of the current collective and submits task for each file to convert. These tasks are submitted with a low priority so that normal processing can still proceed. The body of the request should be empty. 


/sec/item/convertallpdfs

Usage and SDK Samples

secItemIdConfirmPost

Confirms the current meta data of an item.

An item is initially in state "created". The user can confirm the associated data to put it in state "confirmed". 


/sec/item/{id}/confirm

secItemIdCustomfieldPut

Set the value of a custom field.

Sets the value for a custom field to this item. If a value already exists, it is overwritten. A value must comply to the type of the associated field. It must not be the empty string. 


/sec/item/{id}/customfield

secItemIdFolderPut

Set a folder for this item.

Updates the folder property for this item to "place" the item into a folder. If the request contains an empty object or an `id` property of `null`, the item is moved into the "public" or "root" folder. 


/sec/item/{id}/folder

secItemIdProposalsGet

Get a list of proposals for this item.

During text processing, a list of possible meta data has been extracted from each attachment that may be a match to this item. This is returned here, without duplicates. 


/sec/item/{id}/proposals

Usage and SDK Samples

secItemIdTaglinkPost

Link existing tags to an item.

Sets all given tags to the item. The tags must exist, otherwise they are ignored. The tags may be specified as names or ids. 


/sec/item/{id}/taglink

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secItemIdTagsPost

Add a new tag to an item.

Creates a new tag and associates it to the given item. The tag's `id` and `created` are generated and not used from the given data, so it can be left empty. Only `name` and `category` are used, where `category` is optional. 


/sec/item/{id}/tags

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

secItemIdTagsPut

Set new set of tags.

Update the tags associated to an item. This will remove all existing ones and sets the given tags, such that after this returns, the item has exactly the tags as given. 


/sec/item/{id}/tags

secItemIdTagtogglePost

Toggles existing tags to an item.

Toggles all given tags of the item. The tags must exist, otherwise they are ignored. The tags may be specified as names or ids. Tags are either removed or linked from/to the item, depending on whether the item currently is tagged with the corresponding tag. 


/sec/item/{id}/tagtoggle

  • Android

secItemIdUnconfirmPost

Puts an item back to created state.

If an item is confirmed it can be set back to created to appear as new. 


/sec/item/{id}/unconfirm

  • Android

secItemItemIdAttachmentMovebeforePost

Reorder attachments within an item

Moves the `source` attachment before the `target` attachment, such that `source` becomes the immediate neighbor of `target` with a lower position. 


/sec/item/{itemId}/attachment/movebefore

secItemItemIdReprocessPost

Start reprocessing the files of the item.

This submits a job that will re-process the files (either all or the ones specified) of the item and replace the metadata. 


/sec/item/{itemId}/reprocess

secItemSearchIndexPost

Search for items using full-text search only.

Search for items by only using the full-text search index. Unlike the other search routes, this one only asks the full-text search index and returns only one group that contains the results in the same order as given from the index. Most full-text search engines use an ordering that reflect the relevance wrt the search term. The other search routes always order the results by some property (the item date) and thus the relevance ordering is destroyed when using the full-text search. 


/sec/item/searchIndex

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X POST\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
-H "Content-Type: application/json"\
"/api/v1/sec/item/searchIndex"

        ItemApi apiInstance = new ItemApi();
        ItemFtsSearch body = ; // ItemFtsSearch | 
        try {

secItemSearchPost

Search for items.

Search for items given a search form. The results are grouped by month and are sorted by item date (newest first). Tags and attachments are *not* resolved. The results will always contain an empty list for item tags and attachments. Use `/searchWithTags` to also retrieve all tags and a list of attachments of an item. The `fulltext` field can be used to restrict the results by using full-text search in the documents contents. The customfields used in the search query are allowed to be specified by either field id or field name. The values may contain the wildcard `*` at beginning or end. 


/sec/item/search

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android

secItemSearchWithTagsPost

Search for items.

Search for items given a search form. The results are grouped by month by default. For each item, its tags and attachments are also returned. This uses more queries and is therefore slower, but returns all tags to an item as well as their attachments with some minor details. The `fulltext` field can be used to restrict the results by using full-text search in the documents contents. 


/sec/item/searchWithTags

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Android

ItemMultiEdit

secItemsConcEquipmentPut

Sets an equipment to multiple items.

Given an equipment id, sets it on all given items. If no equipment is given, the reference is removed from all given items. 


/sec/items/concEquipment

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secItemsCustomfieldPut

Set the value of a custom field for multiple items

Sets the value for a custom field to multiple given items. If a value already exists, it is overwritten. The value must comply to the associated field type. It must not be the empty string. 


/sec/items/customfield

secItemsCustomfieldremovePost

/sec/items/customfieldremove

secItemsDatePut

Set the date of multiple items

Given multiple item ids and a date, sets it to all items as the item date. If no date is present, remove the date from the items. 


/sec/items/date

Set the direction of multiple items

Given multiple item ids and a direction value, sets it to all items. 


/sec/items/direction

secItemsDuedatePut

Set the direction of multiple items

Given multiple item ids and a date value, sets it to all items as the due date. If the date is missing, remove the due-date from the items. 


/sec/items/duedate

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android

secItemsFolderPut

Sets a folder to multiple items.

Given a folder id, sets it on all given items. If the folder reference is not present, the folder is removed from all items. 


/sec/items/folder

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#

  • Perl
  • Python

secItemsReprocessPost

Submit multiple items to re-processing

Given a list of item-ids, submits all these items for reprocessing. All attachments of these items will be reprocessed. Item metadata is not changed. 


/sec/items/reprocess

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl

secItemsTagsPost

Add tags to multiple items

Add the given tags to all given items. The tags that are currently attached to the items are not changed. If there are new tags in the given list, then they are added. Otherwise, the item is left unchanged. 


/sec/items/tags

Usage and SDK Samples

secItemsTagsremovePut

Sets tags to multiple items

Sets the given tags to all given items. If the tag list is empty, then all tags are removed from the items. 


/sec/items/tagsremove

JobQueue

secQueueIdCancelPost

Cancel a job.

Tries to cancel a job and remove it from the queue. If the job is running, a cancel request is send to the corresponding joex instance. Otherwise the job is removed from the queue. 


/sec/queue/{id}/cancel

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secQueueIdPriorityPost

Change the priority of a waiting job.

A waiting job can change its priority. If the job is not in state waiting, this operation fails. 


/sec/queue/{id}/priority

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android

Get the current state of the job qeue. The job qeue contains all processing tasks and other long-running operations. All users/collectives share processing resources.

Registration

openSignupNewinvitePost

Generate a new invite.

When signup mode is set to "invite", docspell requires an invitation key when signing up. These keys can be created here. Creating such keys requires an admin role, and since docspell has no such concept, a password from the configuration file is required for this action. 


/open/signup/newinvite

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C

secSourcePut

Change an existing source.

Changes an existing source. The source is looked up by its id and all properties are changed as given. 


/sec/source

secTagPost

Create a new tag.

Create a new tag. If a tag with this name already exists, an error is returned. The id in the input structure is ignored. 


/sec/tag

openCheckfileIdChecksumGet

Check if a file is in docspell.

Checks if a file with the given SHA-256 checksum is in docspell. The id is a *source id* configured by a collective. The result shows all items that contains a file with the given checksum. 


/open/checkfile/{id}/{checksum}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/open/checkfile/{id}/{checksum}"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.UploadApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class UploadApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        String checksum = checksum_example; // String | A SHA-256 checksum
        try {
            CheckFileResult result = apiInstance.openCheckfileIdChecksumGet(id, checksum);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#openCheckfileIdChecksumGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

openUploadItemIdPost

Upload files to docspell.

Upload a file to docspell for processing. The id is a *source id* configured by a collective. Files are submitted for processing which eventually resuts in an item in the inbox of the corresponding collective. The request must be a `multipart/form-data` request, where the first part has name `meta`, is optional and may contain upload metadata as JSON. Checkout the structure `ItemUploadMeta` at the end if it is not shown here. Other parts specify the files. Multiple files can be specified, but at least on is required. The upload meta data can be used to tell, whether multiple files are one item, or if each file should become a single item. By default, each file will be a one item. 


/open/upload/item/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X POST\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
-H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data"\
"/api/v1/open/upload/item/{id}"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.UploadApi;

import java.util.*;

public class UploadApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        ItemUploadMeta meta = ; // ItemUploadMeta | 
        array[byte[]] file = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.openUploadItemIdPost(id, meta, file);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#openUploadItemIdPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Upload files to docspell.

Upload a file to docspell for processing. The id is a *source id* configured by a collective. Files are submitted for processing which eventually resuts in an item in the inbox of the corresponding collective. This endpoint associates the files to an existing item identified by its `itemId`. The request must be a `multipart/form-data` request, where the first part has name `meta`, is optional and may contain upload metadata as JSON. Checkout the structure `ItemUploadMeta` at the end if it is not shown here. Other parts specify the files. Multiple files can be specified, but at least on is required. Upload meta data is ignored. 


/open/upload/item/{itemId}/{id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP

-H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data"\
"/api/v1/open/upload/item/{itemId}/{id}"

import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.UploadApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class UploadApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();
        String id = id_example; // String | An identifier
        String itemId = itemId_example; // String | An identifier for an item
        ItemUploadMeta meta = ; // ItemUploadMeta | 
        array[byte[]] file = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.openUploadItemItemIdIdPost(id, itemId, meta, file);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#openUploadItemItemIdIdPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

String *id = id_example; // An identifier
String *itemId = itemId_example; // An identifier for an item
ItemUploadMeta *meta = ; //  (optional)
array[byte[]] *file = ; //  (optional)

UploadApi *apiInstance = [[UploadApi alloc] init];

// Upload files to docspell.
[apiInstance openUploadItemItemIdIdPostWith:id
    itemId:itemId
    meta:meta
    file:file
              completionHandler: ^(BasicResult output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {

                            }
                        }];

            {
                // Upload files to docspell.

            }

            }
        }
    }
}

secCheckfileChecksumGet

Check if a file is in docspell.

Checks if a file with the given SHA-256 checksum is in docspell. The result shows all items that contains a file with the given checksum. 


/sec/checkfile/{checksum}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X GET\
-H "X-Docspell-Auth: [[apiKey]]"\
-H "Accept: application/json"\
"/api/v1/sec/checkfile/{checksum}"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.UploadApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class UploadApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure API key authorization: authTokenHeader
        ApiKeyAuth authTokenHeader = (ApiKeyAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("authTokenHeader");
        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();
        String checksum = checksum_example; // String | A SHA-256 checksum
        try {
            CheckFileResult result = apiInstance.secCheckfileChecksumGet(checksum);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#secCheckfileChecksumGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

                        }];

secUploadItemIdPost

Upload files to docspell.

Upload files to docspell for processing. This route is meant for authenticated users that upload files to their account. This endpoint will associate the files to an existing item identified by its `itemId`. Everything else is the same as with the `/open/upload/item/{itemId}/{id}` endpoint. The request must be a "multipart/form-data" request, where the first part is optional and may contain upload metadata as JSON. Other parts specify the files. Multiple files can be specified, but at least on is required. The upload meta data is ignored, since the item already exists. 


/sec/upload/{itemId}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

"/api/v1/sec/upload/{itemId}"

        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();
        String itemId = itemId_example; // String | An identifier for an item
        ItemUploadMeta meta = ; // ItemUploadMeta | 
        array[byte[]] file = ; // array[byte[]] | 
        try {
            BasicResult result = apiInstance.secUploadItemIdPost(itemId, meta, file);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#secUploadItemIdPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

secUploadItemPost

Upload files to docspell.

Upload files to docspell for processing. This route is meant for authenticated users that upload files to their account. Everything else is the same as with the `/open/upload/item/{id}` endpoint. The request must be a "multipart/form-data" request, where the first part is optional and may contain upload metadata as JSON. Other parts specify the files. Multiple files can be specified, but at least one is required. The upload meta data can be used to tell, whether multiple files are one item, or if each file should become a single item. By default, each file will be a one item. 


/sec/upload/item

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        UploadApi apiInstance = new UploadApi();

        array[byte[]] file = ; // array[byte[]] |

            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UploadApi#secUploadItemPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }

UserTasks

secUsertaskNotifydueitemsGet

Get settings for "Notify Due Items" task

Return the current notification settings of the authenticated user. Users can be notified on due items via e-mail. This is done by periodically querying items. It is possible to have multiple tasks. 


/sec/usertask/notifydueitems

/sec/usertask/notifydueitems

secUsertaskNotifydueitemsStartoncePost

Start the "Notify Due Items" task once

Starts the notify-due-items task just once, discarding the schedule and not updating the periodic task. 


/sec/usertask/notifydueitems/startonce

secUsertaskScanmailboxGet

Get settings for "Scan Mailbox" task

Return the current settings for the scan-mailbox tasks of the authenticated user. Users can periodically fetch mails to be imported into docspell. It is possible to have multiple of these tasks. 


/sec/usertask/scanmailbox

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#

        authTokenHeader.setApiKey("YOUR API KEY");
        // Uncomment the following line to set a prefix for the API key, e.g. "Token" (defaults to null)
        //authTokenHeader.setApiKeyPrefix("Token");

        UserTasksApi apiInstance = new UserTasksApi();
        try {
            ScanMailboxSettingsList result = apiInstance.secUsertaskScanmailboxGet();
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling UserTasksApi#secUsertaskScanmailboxGet");
            e.printStackTrace();

Get settings for "Scan Mailbox" task

Return the current settings for a single scan-mailbox task of the authenticated user. Users can periodically fetch mails to be imported into docspell. 


/sec/usertask/scanmailbox/{id}

secUsertaskScanmailboxStartoncePost

Start the "Scan Mailbox" task once

Starts the scan-mailbox task just once, discarding the schedule and not updating the periodic task. 


/sec/usertask/scanmailbox/startonce

Utility

secCaleventCheckPost

Check a calendar event string

For ui purposes, this route checks a calendar event string and either returns the normal form or an error message. 


/sec/calevent/check
